commentary: Cottrell to Dhawan, OUT big appeal but the umpire is disinterested. Full, on off, and Dhawan had prodded forward to defend, but the ball hit his pads. Conference between the WI players and Holder goes for a review! Definitely looked like an inside edge on first glance, but what do the replays show? Oooooh, it looks like front pad-back pad, and no bat involved. Impact in front of off stump, and that is smashing into middle stump. Epic review - Dhawan goes!

commentary: Kumar to Gayle, OUT Gayle has reviewed an lbw decision. That was full and on middle stump. Sounded like an inside edge, but Gayle took some time to think about it, so that's out of the question I suppose. He's struck right in front of middle...is it pitching in line? Just. The decision will stand. And the review is gone. As is Gayle. Bhuvneshwar strikes. India wanted Shami to bowl this over, but he'd been off the field for a bit and wasn't back in time to come straight on. Inadvertently, it has worked. Full ball pitching on leg, skidding on and rapping him. He was just hanging the bat out without a stride

commentary: Mohammed Shami to Chase, 4 runs overthrows. Short of a length on off, pulled straight to midwicket where Iyer picks cleanly on the bounce and chucks it at the non-striker's end. commentary: Kumar to Chase, OUT plucks that out of the air, horizontal to his left! Wow! Bhuvneshwar Kumar! Flipped the game in five minutes. Length ball at off and middle. He wants to turn this into the leg side, but it sticks in the pitch. And it floats back off the shoulder of his bat. It's very far to the bowler's left, but he's managed to steady himself and go full stretch, one-handed. And he's held on. Back up quickly with a sheepish grin. Superb.
